From d001ec1d43312b8ab5422643c44a7addc8ed91cb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: forsen <gazikkamalov2@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 02:10:52 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] vtest: raise listen backlog to 128

A backlog of 1 makes concurrent client connect()s fail or stall during
an Android boot storm (tens of HWUI processes connecting simultaneously),
which surfaced as intermittent vkCreateInstance/vkCreateDevice failures
in guests.
---
 vtest/vtest_server.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vtest/vtest_server.c b/vtest/vtest_server.c
index 8685d33..dcf1b19 100644
--- a/vtest/vtest_server.c
+++ b/vtest/vtest_server.c
@@ -422,7 +422,7 @@ static void vtest_server_open_socket(void)
       goto err;
    }
 
-   if (listen(server.socket, 1) < 0){
+   if (listen(server.socket, 128) < 0){
       goto err;
    }
 
